 Here, we need to combine like terms. We have \( 3p^3 - 5p + 6 + 4 - 6p^2 + 2p \). First, we combine like terms: \begin{align*}
3p^3 - 6p^2 - 5p + 2p + 6 + 4 &= 3p^3 - 6p^2 - 3p + 10
\end{align*} <answer> The answer is $3p^3 - 6p^2 - 3p + 10$. </answer>

